verses.text_plain: And after Abimelech there arose to defend Israel Tola the son of Puah, the son of Dodo, a man of Issachar; and he dwelt in Shamir in mount Ephraim.
verses.verse_html:
1And after Abimelech there arose to defend Israel Tola the son of Puah, the son of Dodo, a man of Issachar; and he dwelt in Shamir in mount Ephraim. ▼
▼ defend: or, deliver: Heb. save

footnotes.body_html: ▼ defend: or, deliver: Heb. save

verses.text_plain: And he judged Israel twenty and three years, and died, and was buried in Shamir.
verses.verse_html: 2And he judged Israel twenty and three years, and died, and was buried in Shamir.

verses.text_plain: And after him arose Jair, a Gileadite, and judged Israel twenty and two years.
verses.verse_html: 3And after him arose Jair, a Gileadite, and judged Israel twenty and two years.

verses.text_plain: And he had thirty sons that rode on thirty ass colts, and they had thirty cities, which are called Havoth–jair unto this day, which are in the land of Gilead.
verses.verse_html:
4And he had thirty sons that rode on thirty ass colts, and they had thirty cities, which are called Havoth–jair unto this day, which are in the land of Gilead. ▼
▼ Havoth–jair: or, the villages of Jair

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Havoth–jair: or, the villages of Jair
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Havoth–jair: or, the villages of Jair

verses.text_plain: And Jair died, and was buried in Camon.
verses.verse_html: 5And Jair died, and was buried in Camon.

verses.text_plain: And the children of Israel did evil again in the sight of the Lord, and served Baalim, and Ashtaroth, and the gods of Syria, and the gods of Zidon, and the gods of Moab, and the gods of the children of Ammon, and the gods of the Philistines, and forsook the Lord, and served not him.
verses.verse_html: 6And the children of Israel did evil again in the sight of the Lord, and served Baalim, and Ashtaroth, and the gods of Syria, and the gods of Zidon, and the gods of Moab, and the gods of the children of Ammon, and the gods of the Philistines, and forsook the Lord, and served not him.

verses.text_plain: And the anger of the Lord was hot against Israel, and he sold them into the hands of the Philistines, and into the hands of the children of Ammon.
verses.verse_html: 7And the anger of the Lord was hot against Israel, and he sold them into the hands of the Philistines, and into the hands of the children of Ammon.

verses.text_plain: And that year they vexed and oppressed the children of Israel: eighteen years, all the children of Israel that were on the other side Jordan in the land of the Amorites, which is in Gilead.
verses.verse_html:
8And that year they vexed and oppressed the children of Israel: eighteen years, all the children of Israel that were on the other side Jordan in the land of the Amorites, which is in Gilead. ▼
▼ oppressed: Heb. crushed

verses.text_plain: Moreover the children of Ammon passed over Jordan to fight also against Judah, and against Benjamin, and against the house of Ephraim; so that Israel was sore distressed.
verses.verse_html: 9Moreover the children of Ammon passed over Jordan to fight also against Judah, and against Benjamin, and against the house of Ephraim; so that Israel was sore distressed.

verses.text_plain: And the children of Israel cried unto the Lord, saying, We have sinned against thee, both because we have forsaken our God, and also served Baalim.
verses.verse_html: 10And the children of Israel cried unto the Lord, saying, We have sinned against thee, both because we have forsaken our God, and also served Baalim.

tokens.text: against thee, both because we have forsaken

verses.text_plain: And the Lord said unto the children of Israel, Did not I deliver you from the Egyptians, and from the Amorites, from the children of Ammon, and from the Philistines?
verses.verse_html: 11And the Lord said unto the children of Israel, Did not I deliver you from the Egyptians, and from the Amorites, from the children of Ammon, and from the Philistines?

verses.text_plain: The Zidonians also, and the Amalekites, and the Maonites, did oppress you; and ye cried to me, and I delivered you out of their hand.
verses.verse_html: 12The Zidonians also, and the Amalekites, and the Maonites, did oppress you; and ye cried to me, and I delivered you out of their hand.

verses.text_plain: Yet ye have forsaken me, and served other gods: wherefore I will deliver you no more.
verses.verse_html: 13Yet ye have forsaken me, and served other gods: wherefore I will deliver you no more.

verses.text_plain: Go and cry unto the gods which ye have chosen; let them deliver you in the time of your tribulation.
verses.verse_html: 14Go and cry unto the gods which ye have chosen; let them deliver you in the time of your tribulation.

verses.text_plain: And the children of Israel said unto the Lord, We have sinned: do thou unto us whatsoever seemeth good unto thee; deliver us only, we pray thee, this day.
verses.verse_html:
15And the children of Israel said unto the Lord, We have sinned: do thou unto us whatsoever seemeth good unto thee; deliver us only, we pray thee, this day. ▼
▼ seemeth…: Heb. is good in thine eyes

tokens.text: us only, we pray thee, this day

footnotes.body_text: ▼ seemeth…: Heb. is good in thine eyes
footnotes.body_html: ▼ seemeth…: Heb. is good in thine eyes

verses.text_plain: And they put away the strange gods from among them, and served the Lord: and his soul was grieved for the misery of Israel.
verses.verse_html:
16And they put away the strange gods from among them, and served the Lord: and his soul was grieved for the misery of Israel. ▼
▼ strange…: Heb. gods of strangers
 , ▼
▼ grieved: Heb. shortened

footnotes.body_html: ▼ strange…: Heb. gods of strangers

verses.text_plain: Then the children of Ammon were gathered together, and encamped in Gilead. And the children of Israel assembled themselves together, and encamped in Mizpeh.
verses.verse_html:
17Then the children of Ammon were gathered together, and encamped in Gilead. And the children of Israel assembled themselves together, and encamped in Mizpeh. ▼
▼ gathered: Heb. cried

verses.text_plain: And the people and princes of Gilead said one to another, What man is he that will begin to fight against the children of Ammon? he shall be head over all the inhabitants of Gilead.
verses.verse_html: 18And the people and princes of Gilead said one to another, What man is he that will begin to fight against the children of Ammon? he shall be head over all the inhabitants of Gilead.
